### Step 4 вЂ” Register the MCP with Claude Code

Add an entry to `~/.claude.json` under `mcpServers`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "<service-name>": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "<spawn command>",
      "args": ["<arg1>", "<arg2>"],
      "env": {
        "<ENV_VAR_1>": "<value from earlier step>",
        "<ENV_VAR_2>": "<value from earlier step>"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Or use the helper:

```bash
./scripts/configure.sh
```

It prompts for the values, patches `~/.claude.json`, and validates before returning.

Restart Claude Code so it picks up the new MCP.

